<Docs title="Quickstart" description="Get Hippocampus running in minutes on Linux using the native binary or Docker.">
  <h1 id="quickstart">Quickstart</h1>
  <p>
    Hippocampus runs fully local and exposes both a CLI and HTTP/gRPC APIs.
    Native binary packages are provided for <strong>Linux x86-64</strong>.
    Docker is the recommended path for macOS and Windows until native builds are available for those platforms.
  </p>

  <h2 id="option-a-linux-binary">Option A &mdash; Linux binary (recommended for Linux)</h2>

  <h3 id="1-download-and-extract">1. Download and extract</h3>
  <pre><code>curl -fL https://github.com/theQuarky/hippocampus/releases/latest/download/hippocampus-v0.1.0-linux-x64.tar.gz \
  | tar -xz -C ~/hippocampus --strip-components=0
cd ~/hippocampus</code></pre>

  <h3 id="2-start-qdrant">2. Start Qdrant (vector store)</h3>
  <p>
    The binary expects Qdrant on <code>http://localhost:6333</code>.
    The fastest way to start it is with Docker:
  </p>
  <pre><code>docker run -d --name qdrant -p 6333:6333 -p 6334:6334 \
  -v "$(pwd)/qdrant-data:/qdrant/storage" \
  qdrant/qdrant:latest</code></pre>

  <h3 id="3-start-ollama">3. Start Ollama (local LLM)</h3>
  <pre><code># Install Ollama from https://ollama.com/download if not already installed
ollama serve &amp;
ollama pull phi3:mini
ollama pull moondream</code></pre>

  <h3 id="4-run-hippocampus">4. Run Hippocampus</h3>
  <pre><code>./hippocampus-server-linux
# HTTP API  → http://localhost:3001
# gRPC      → localhost:50051</code></pre>

  <h3 id="5-ingest-and-query">5. Ingest and query</h3>
  <pre><code># Ingest a file
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/ingest/url \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '&#123;"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippocampus"&#125;'

# Ask a grounded question
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/query-answer \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '&#123;"question":"What is the hippocampus?"&#125;'</code></pre>

  <h2 id="other-linux-packages">Other Linux packages</h2>

  <h3 id="appimage">AppImage &mdash; self-contained runner</h3>
  <p>
    The AppImage wraps the server binary in a launcher script (<code>AppRun</code>) that also accepts CLI arguments.
    It does <strong>not</strong> bundle Qdrant or Ollama — you still need those running first (see steps 2&ndash;3 above).
  </p>
  <pre><code>chmod +x Hippocampus-*.AppImage

# Start the HTTP + gRPC server
./Hippocampus-*.AppImage

# Or run CLI commands directly
./Hippocampus-*.AppImage ingest https://example.com
./Hippocampus-*.AppImage query-answer "What is X?"</code></pre>

  <h3 id="deb">.deb &mdash; GUI desktop installer</h3>
  <p>
    The <code>.deb</code> package installs an Electron-based graphical setup application to <code>/opt/Hippocampus/</code>.
    It is a <strong>GUI wizard</strong>, not the headless CLI server.
    Use the tar.gz or AppImage if you need a server process or CLI access.
  </p>
  <pre><code>sudo dpkg -i hippocampus-installer_*_amd64.deb
hippocampus-installer</code></pre>

  <h2 id="option-b-docker">Option B &mdash; Docker (all platforms)</h2>

  <h3 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Docker and Docker Compose</li>
    <li>At least 8 GB RAM recommended</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 id="start-services">Start services</h3>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/theQuarky/hippocampus.git
cd hippocampus

npm run docker:up
npm run docker:setup</code></pre>
  <p>
    This starts Qdrant, Ollama, and Hippocampus, then pulls the default local models.
  </p>

  <h3 id="ingest-and-query-docker">Ingest and query via Docker</h3>
  <pre><code>npm run docker:ingest -- ingest /uploads/example.pdf
npm run docker:ingest -- query-answer "What are the main points?"</code></pre>

  <h2 id="api-endpoints">API Endpoints</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>HTTP API: <code>http://localhost:3001</code></li>
    <li>gRPC API: <code>localhost:50051</code></li>
    <li>Qdrant: <code>http://localhost:6333</code></li>
    <li>Ollama: <code>http://localhost:11434</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="local-development">Local Development (from source)</h2>
  <pre><code>docker compose up -d qdrant ollama
npm install
npm run build
npm run ingest -- ./path/to/file.pdf
npm run query-answer -- "What is this document about?"</code></pre>
</Docs>
